  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2014-06-10", 
    "text": "Highway Runoff Management Act - Requires each state to develop for approval a state highway stormwater management program consisting of management measures to prevent, reduce, or control highway runoff from federal-aid highway projects.\n\nDirects the Secretary of Transportation (DOT) to publish guidance to assist states in the establishment of such measures."
